# Project structure rules — see AGENTS.md for full details

## Build & Verify
```bash
npx tsc --noEmit        # type check — must be clean before committing
npm test                # run vitest + DOM binding checker
```

## Layer Architecture (top → bottom, strictly)
```
src/main.ts              Bootstrap
  ↓ src/ui/*             DOM, events, Canvas
  ↓ src/state.ts, src/optimizer.ts, src/temporalState.ts   Business logic
  ↓ src/engine.ts, src/exposure.ts, src/temporalQuantize.ts   Pure math
  ↓ src/constants.ts, src/types.ts   Base definitions
  ↓ presets/             Static data — imports NOTHING from src/
```

No upward imports. No circular deps. Pure math files (engine, exposure, temporalQuantize) may ONLY import from constants.ts and types.ts.

## Where New Code Goes
| Concern | File |
|---|---|
| Types / interfaces | `src/types.ts` |
| Physics constants, range limits, shared utils | `src/constants.ts` |
| Spatial math (MTF, diffraction, FOV) | `src/engine.ts` |
| Exposure math (SNR, photons, dark current) | `src/exposure.ts` |
| Camera optimizer | `src/optimizer.ts` |
| Motion params, fps/shutter/region state | `src/temporalState.ts` |
| FPS/shutter region math | `src/temporalQuantize.ts` |
| Global app state, presets, setters | `src/state.ts` |
| App bootstrap, tab switching | `src/main.ts` |
| One DOM panel / concern | `src/ui/<name>.ts` |
| Shared DOM helpers | `src/ui/domUtils.ts` |
| Shared Canvas helpers | `src/ui/canvasUtils.ts` |
| Static preset JSON | `presets/<type>/<name>.json` |
| Preset loaders | `presets/<type>s.ts` |
| Unit tests | `tests/<name>.test.ts` |
| E2e tests | `e2e/<name>.spec.ts` |

## Code Re-use — Use These Before Writing Inline
- `clamped(val, min, max)` from `constants.ts` — instead of `Math.max/min`
- `clampStep(val, min, max, step)` from `constants.ts` — stepped clamp
- `chromaSnrPenaltyDb(state)` / `chromaFormatEfficiencyPenalty(state)` from `constants.ts` — chroma penalty
- `computeImageVelocity(motion, shutterTime, focalLength, distance)` from `engine.ts` — vEff/vRot/vTotal/vImg
- `motionHeadroom(motion, fps, errorBudgetMm)` from `optimizer.ts` — maxAccel/maxTurn
- `setText(id, text)` from `ui/outputs.ts` — set element text content
- `setInputIfNotFocused(id, value)` from `ui/domUtils.ts` — set input value safely
- Hardcoded data tables go in `constants.ts` or `presets/`, never in UI files
- Preset loader wrappers: use direct `as T` cast, not a wrapper function

## DOM Binding Rules
- `tests/dom-bindings.test.ts` enforces bidirectional consistency between HTML IDs and TS `getElementById` calls
- Must pass before any commit touching `index.html` or `src/ui/`
- DOM ID naming: kebab-case preferred; camelCase OK for IDs matching `AppState` property names
- Dynamic elements use `data-*` attributes, not auto-generated IDs
- Use `setInputIfNotFocused` from `domUtils.ts` for setting inputs without focus steal
- Use `setText` from `outputs.ts` for setting text content

## Naming
- DOM IDs: kebab-case (`exp-snr-bar`); camelCase for domain-model fields (`focalLength`)
- Functions/variables: camelCase (`calculateResults`, `shutterDenom`)
- Interfaces/types: PascalCase (`AppState`, `MotionParams`)
- Constants: UPPER_SNAKE_CASE (`SNR_DB_MAX`)
- Source files: camelCase matching primary export
